HEADWORD: Sulphoarsenic
<hw>Sul`pho*ar*sen"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or containing, sulphur and
arsenic; -- said of an acid which is the same as arsenic acid with the
substitution of sulphur for oxygen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sulphocarbonate</ent>⟦br⟧
